		{
			dependencies: ["70983AD660631855"]
			description: [
				"  Here, things are rarely as simple as “play a mod and move on.” Progress unfolds in &asets of three chapters&r, each focused on mastering the essentials of one or more mods. Within each trio there is some freedom — you can explore them in parallel if you wish. Still, the next group will usually assume those essentials are already in your hands. There are exceptions… though even those tend to follow a logic you only recognize when it's too late."
				""
				"  Alongside these trios are the &l&4TECH chapters&r&r, which expand on what you unlock in the main progression veins. Some introduce quality-of-life upgrades or direct improvements to machines and components you already use. Others reveal interesting mechanics or alternative production paths. And a few… well, you will quickly realize they are simply &7&otoo useful to live without.&r&r"
				""
				"  This modpack was not made to be rushed, but to be chewed slowly. It rewards solving one thing at a time, without anxiety about reaching the end. The goal is not simply to “finish,” but to lose yourself in the process: quests that guide while entertaining, and mods woven together into a single ecosystem. Nothing here stands alone — everything forms part of a larger machine that responds to each step you take."
				""
				"  And in the end, this is not just about progress. Every structure you build becomes another vertebra of something that was always there, only fragmented. You read, construct, complete. And what appears to be instruction may simply be the echo of your own writing."
			]
			icon: "kubejs:mechanical_heart"
			id: "22E8C8BE07968048"
			subtitle: "A book that likes order"
			tasks: [{
				id: "44694809009FB5DE"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			title: "The Essential Flow"
			x: -11.5d
			y: -4.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["22E8C8BE07968048"]
			description: [
				"  The &4&lTECH&r&r chapters run parallel to the main progression — small utility detours, a curious appendix in the middle of an otherwise orderly path. They do not dictate the route, but they offer shortcuts, tools, and clever tricks that make the journey less rough… or simply more enjoyable."
				""
				"  After every set of three main chapters, these side paths appear. They build on what you have already unlocked, often showing that even things that once seemed superfluous can find their place."
				""
				"  These chapters mirror key milestones from the main progression, almost acting as markers of how far you have advanced through the numbered veins. They expand the technologies you unlocked to embrace their full potential!"
				"  "
				"  &4&lWARNING:&r&r TECH chapters are currently deeply incomplete or missleading in this build. &mPlease help me.&r "
				""
				"&7&o— You call them optional. I prefer to think of them as carefully calculated distractions.&r&r"
			]
			icon: {
				Count: 1
				id: "actuallyadditions:laser_wrench"
				tag: { }
			}
			id: "07A61EFA0186CB52"
			tasks: [{
				id: "5C9E8DD8C08B11AB"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			title: "A Brief Aside"
			x: -10.5d
			y: -4.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["7E88E307D7B20E6B"]
			description: [
				"  A passive and reliable way to slowly restore ambient aura. These enchanted trees draw energy from deeper places, releasing it back into the world as they grow. They are magical, but not immortal — with heavy use, their leaves will wither and fall in time. Treat them well, and they’ll withstand the strain with quiet resilience. And yes, they are as beautiful as they are useful."
				""
				"&7&o— Even miracles shed leaves.&r&r"
			]
			id: "33FDC0F2FD47BA47"
			shape: "square"
			tasks: [{
				id: "3EF867CD949093BD"
				item: "naturesaura:ancient_sapling"
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: -0.5d
			y: 2.3428571428571274d
		}
		{
			dependencies: [
				"462BCAE24399B514"
				"5EC81561779BCF73"
			]
			description: [
				"  The Natural Altar is your first method of channeling ambient aura into tangible transformation. Place items upon it to convert them using the energy suspended in the world around you. But be warned — each ritual &4drains&r the surrounding aura. Without ways to replenish it, the land may react in unpleasant and aggressive ways."
				""
				"  To simplify construction, open the Book of Natural Aura, find the altar entry, and click the small eye near the structure. This will project a guide into the world so you can build the multiblock accurately."
				""
				"  While the outer blocks must remain unchanged, the block directly beneath the altar may be replaced with &l&8hoppers&r&r or other item transport method — making automation not only possible, but inevitable."
				""
				"&7&o— Aura appreciates tradition. But it tolerates a well-placed hopper.&r&r"
			]
			hide_dependency_lines: true
			id: "7E88E307D7B20E6B"
			shape: "square"
			size: 1.0d
			tasks: [{
				id: "11967428B0D78714"
				item: "naturesaura:nature_altar"
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: -1.0d
			y: 1.3428571428571274d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["7E88E307D7B20E6B"]
			description: [
				"  Plain iron holds structure, but lacks spirit. By placing it upon the Natural Altar, ambient aura infuses the metal with properties it never possessed — stronger, more receptive, and attuned to deeper rituals."
				""
				"  This is your first true transformation through aura. Remember: the power used must return to the land, one way or another."
				""
				"&7&o— Iron obeys force. Infused iron obeys intention.&r&r"
			]
			id: "3720B8882392764A"
			shape: "square"
			tasks: [{
				id: "214F7B3719194C0B"
				item: "naturesaura:infused_iron"
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: 0.0d
			y: 1.3428571428571274d
		}
		{
			dependencies: [
				"1E44769B1B4BAFA4"
				"18DF48C8A8B52BA2"
			]
			description: [
				"  To bridge the mortal and the divine, even simple gestures matter. Build a flowered clearing as the book suggests — colors and patterns left to your interpretation. With the Offering Table at its center, you may present objects to higher forces and receive something more elaborate in return. Whether it’s generosity or a cosmic joke remains uncertain."
				""
				"  Place the offering with &aright-click&r, then drop a &bSpirit of Calling&r onto the pillar to begin. After a short moment, the items will be consumed in a bolt of lightning, and your reward will fall from above. You can offer &2up to 16&r of the same item at once using a &2single Spirit of Calling&r — frugal worship at its finest. The ritual can be &8&lautomated&r&r with modest redstone and creativity."
				""
				"&7&o— Our humble junk becomes their humble junk, returned with ceremony.&r&r"
			]
			id: "021D8AC2257200B6"
			shape: "square"
			tasks: [{
				id: "26012A39BB03BEC0"
				item: "naturesaura:offering_table"
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: 3.5d
			y: -1.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["5FD7CCD89895AAAB"]
			description: [
				"  The first and most familiar aura you will encounter is Bottled Sunlight — the distilled essence of the Overworld. &aRight-click&r with a Bottle and Crock while in this realm to collect it."
				""
				"  This process can be &l&8automated&r&r with ease: a humble dispenser with the tool inside performs the capture unattended. Deities and aura seem to appreciate primitive contraptions."
				""
				"&7&o— The gods show restraint. They only ask for the sky in a bottle.&r&r"
			]
			icon: {
				Count: 1
				id: "naturesaura:aura_bottle"
				tag: {
					stored_type: "naturesaura:overworld"
				}
			}
			id: "5BF0B3134EF672C0"
			shape: "circle"
			tasks: [{
				id: "789D21DBBE3A1EBC"
				item: {
					Count: 1
					id: "naturesaura:aura_bottle"
					tag: {
						stored_type: "naturesaura:overworld"
					}
				}
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: 0.0d
			y: -3.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["5BF0B3134EF672C0"]
			description: [
				"  A small token used to address the forces beyond your reach. Tossed not as payment, but as a request — or perhaps an invitation. Whether the higher powers answer out of compassion, curiosity, or amusement is unclear, but they do answer."
				""
				"&7&o— Prayer works better when it makes noise.&r&r"
			]
			id: "1E44769B1B4BAFA4"
