			}]
			x: -1.5d
			y: 2.3428571428571274d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["36ED84D6DA1ACBF6"]
			description: [
				"  Some plants respond not to water or sunlight, but to sacrifice. The &dRose Needle&r is your tool for coaxing life into unfamiliar shapes. Hold it and &aright-click&r a planted &awheat seed&r — a single, delicate drop of blood is enough to trigger the change."
				""
				"  This is the fastest way to obtain vital herbs: plants with unique properties used in many rites and recipes. The transformation &amay produce either&r Bleeding Heart or Needle Heart at random, so repeat the ritual until you have what you need. Once acquired, cultivate them carefully — they will matter more than they appear to now."
				""
				"&7&o— Growth demands patience. And occasionally, a finger prick.&r&r"
			]
			icon: "kubejs:rose_needle"
			id: "0D69EDFAA244A42E"
			tasks: [
				{
					id: "037EFD759C9FA947"
					item: "kubejs:rose_needle"
					type: "item"
				}
				{
					id: "5001C490226E85D9"
					item: "vital_herbs:bleeding_heart"
					type: "item"
				}
				{
					id: "3FC92D3FDBF7C4F5"
					item: "vital_herbs:needle_heart"
					type: "item"
				}
			]
			x: -1.0d
			y: -1.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["042EC538643F435A"]
			description: [
				"  The chaos of raw stone hides patterns that the naked eye refuses to see. Ancient miners learned to separate dirt from &lpromise,&r and promise from true &lmetal.&r This bench is your introduction to that quiet art. A place where rough minerals are sorted, broken down, and persuaded to reveal their composite nature."
				""
				"  Drop a &6Crafting Table&r into &bwater&r with &5me&r as catalyst. The JEI entry will make it look like I'm consumed in the transformation — dramatically, I might add. I'm not. &m&7Probably&r.&r"
				""
				"  Once you have the Ore Sorting Bench, place your ores there and watch them fracture into recognizable mineral compounds. It may look primitive, but many great discoveries begin with a rock, a tool, and the unsettling suspicion that the rock is &clying.&r"
				""
				"&7&o— If you thought ores came ready to smelt, you're adorably mistaken.&r"
			]
			id: "155BB7639312253D"
			shape: "gear"
			tasks: [{
				id: "289CD381A5E9C0E8"
				item: {
					Count: 1
					id: "custommachinery:custom_machine_item"
					tag: {
						machine: "custommachinery:ore_bench"
					}
				}
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "Rock Solid Lies"
			x: -3.0d
			y: -1.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["155BB7639312253D"]
			description: [
				"  This land is &4old,&r and its metals are no longer found in pure form. Ages of upheaval fused once-separate veins into mixed mineral compounds."
				""
				"  The core metals you need are locked inside these mixtures. To obtain them, you must sort and break down the compounds first. Open the Ore Sorting Bench recipes by &aclicking U&r in a ore composite or clicking the progress bar in the bench itself. — there you can see every mineral compound and which usable metals each one produces. "
				""
				"&7&o— You call it “modded.” The planet calls it “trauma.”&r&r"
			]
			id: "36ED84D6DA1ACBF6"
			shape: "gear"
			tasks: [
				{
					id: "526E3B892270476F"
					item: "minecraft:raw_iron"
					type: "item"
				}
				{
					id: "63CDE00386925B3C"
					item: "kubejs:hematite_raw"
					type: "item"
				}
			]
			x: -2.0d
			y: -1.0d
		}
		{
			description: [
				"  &l&5Mechanized Depths&r&r is currently in active development, and this version exists primarily for &lplaytesting.&r"
				""
				"  The design philosophy of the pack aims to create a progression that starts relatively smooth and approachable, gradually increasing in complexity as the player gains access to better tools, machines, and automation systems. The goal is to reward infrastructure building, experimentation, and thoughtful automation rather than repetitive grinding."
				""
				"  If you are looking for a fully polished and carefully balanced experience, you may prefer waiting for an official release. That said, the pack is already very much \"\"playable\"\"."
				""
				"  Chapters &21&r through &28&r (out of &421&r planned chapters) are currently structured and the main progression through them is well established. Not every quest has full descriptions yet, some mechanics might — and probably will — change, but all of this will be addressed and implemented gradually as development continues."
				""
				"  And... Yeah, I know. The playtest ends right when things start to get &l&4f&r&r&l&dr&r&r&l&ee&r&r&l&da&r&r&l&bk&r&r&l&ay&r&r and actually unique. I really wanted to have more playable content, especially where the systems begin to diverge from the usual progression trees and the custom mechanics shine. But I also need to start gathering feedback to validate and refine what’s already here. At some point, I realized that if I keep gatekeeping the pack until it has everything I want… it’s never getting done. So playtesting it is. "
				""
				"  Anyways, If you're here, you're already part of making this pack better."
				""
				"  Thank you for taking the time to try it out and help shape its future &l&a:)&r&r"
			]
			icon: "kubejs:minerva"
			id: "36B004CC913D8CC7"
			shape: "square"
			tasks: [{
				id: "4E03077442D29486"
				type: "checkmark"
			}]
			title: "Overal info!"
			x: -3.5d
			y: -7.0d
		}
		{
			description: [
				"  While Chapters 1 through 8 represent the currently playable progression, many of the later chapters are already present in this build as well."
				""
				"  Some of them contain notes describing ideas, concepts, or systems currently being developed. Others are simply structural placeholders or isolated quests that exist out of order as part of the pack's internal framework."
				""
				"  If you are curious and want to explore these experimental sections — or see parts of the pack's backbone systems (such as the quest hooks used for book interactions and game stage control) — you can do so easily."
				""
				"  Simply enter a world with &acheats enabled&r, open the FTB Quests interface, and click \"&aEnable editing mode&r\" in the &abottom-right corner&r of the HUD."
				""
				"  This will allow you to browse the full quest structure and take a look at features that are still under development."
			]
